<section class="summary" id="sect-00003">
<title>Section Summary</title>
<para id="para-00016">A new populism took shape with the candidacy of Donald Trump. Viewed as an outsider and facing opposition even from within his own party, Trump overcame a massive primary field and went on to defeat Hillary Clinton in an election that greatly differed from previous cycles. Trump’s policies and practices led to widespread protests and government opposition. Overt and public racism came to light in the Unite the Right Rally, which devolved into violence and was broken up by the National Guard. Movements such as MeToo rose in popularity largely through social media, often leading to greater awareness and interest, but not always contributing to the movements’ goals.</para>
</section>
