  <problem id="prob-00001">
  <para id="para-00017">Considering that at the time, the United States was working to reduce its military presence and investment in the Middle East, what were the most likely rationales for the U.S. and its allies’ increased activity in the reaction to the rise of ISIS in Iraq and Afghanistan? What role may public perception have played?</para></problem>
  </exercise>
  <exercise id="exer-00002">
  <problem id="prob-00002">
  <para id="para-00018">Activism and commentary on social media can be considered a historical record. Considering the historical amnesia that occurred following events like the Tulsa Massacre, is it more or less likely that the events in the social media era will be forgotten or obscured?</para></problem>
